28465,75579,75275,34919,75102,33603,36962,55888],"tags":[268435469],"category":0,"genres":[13],"first_release_date":1267488000000,"pulse_count":1,"platforms":[6],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":6,"date":1267488000000,"region":8,"human":"2010-Mar-02","y":2010,"m":3}],"screenshots":[{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/sqxrfn76mv6d54gfohe7.jpg","cloudinary_id":"sqxrfn76mv6d54gfohe7","width":800,"height":450},{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/qfxfjnldqeyzyazug1ix.jpg","cloudinary_id":"qfxfjnldqeyzyazug1ix","width":800,"height":450},{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/r0ydgffdmw3rbd41vbuv.jpg","cloudinary_id":"r0ydgffdmw3rbd41vbuv","width":800,"height":450}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/jfacty11gor09t3yir6z.jpg","cloudinary_id":"jfacty11gor09t3yir6z","width":867,"height":1200}},{"id":50409,"name":"Battle Isle IV: The Andosia War","slug":"battle-isle-iv-the-andosia-war","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/battle-isle-iv-the-andosia-war","created_at":1500041373374,"updated_at":1500462395737,"summary":"The first three games are played on a hexagonal grid for a map. Players not only control the combat units (ranging from infantry and tanks to helicopters, fighters and bombers, armored trains, surface warships and submarines, stationary gun turrets), but (especially in the later games) also many support logistics units (ammo and fuel transports, scout and radar units, road and construction vehicles, and others). Units have various weapons and can gain experience (which in later games can be transferred over in a campaign). Fuel and ammo is limited, and logistics require careful attention. Players also control buildings, where units can be repaired, and sometimes, produced. Weather conditions change, affecting unit movements (for example, a sea or river can freeze, immobilizing ships but allowing light units to move through it). Fog of war is prevalent and players have to use scouting units to gain information about the battlefield. Some of those options were added in expansions or sequels. \n \nPlayers have various tasks, ranging from eliminating all opponent forces to capturing specific buildings or protecting certain units or places. In some missions events from outside the battlefield can suddenly change the situation, giving players new objectives, reinforcements, allies or enemies. In some battles there are more than two sides, each with their own objectives, not all of them directly involved in hostilities - some of them can be even allied. At the same time, those allegiances can change because of some events or actions. \n \nBattle Isle one had the screen divided into two parts, one for each player. The turns were also divided into move and attack phases. While one player moved his units, the other commanded his own troops to carry out his actions. Battle Isle 2 gave the player the entire screen, and merged move and attack phases, and introduced the 3-D display of combat. Battle Isle 3 was very similar to Battle Isle 2, with improved graphics, more units and a new storyline. Battle Isle: The Andosian War was entirely set in the 3-D environment and combined elements of real-time and turn-based strategies. \n \nThe AI is relatively weak, relying on mass frontal assaults. After a player survives the first few turns and the AI's overwhelming numbers using protected artillery and terrain advantage, the computer is usually unable to mount a proper defense.","popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[11362,73075,9760,33603,36962,55888,65827,2015,32283,33383],"tags":[268435471],"category":0,"genres":[15],"first_release_date":975628800000,"platforms":[6],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":6,"date":975628800000,"region":8,"human":"2000-Dec-01","y":2000,"m":12}]},{"id":50410,"name":"London Underground Simulator - World of Subways Vol.3","slug":"london-underground-simulator-world-of-subways-vol-dot-3","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/london-underground-simulator-world-of-subways-vol-dot-3","created_at":1500041378121,"updated_at":1500462469030,"summary":"World of Subways\" is our series of the most interesting Subway and Underground routes of the world for the PC. After the releases of New York and Berlin we are now proud to introduce Vol.3 - London Underground. This simulation covers the entire Circle Line in its current operational service which includes the new section to Hammersmith. This line offers a length of 27km with 35 stations, many hours of fun and interesting missions. \n \nThe Circle Line is an underground service of the London Underground circling the center of London. It was first described as such in 1949 and already appeared on the 1947 Underground Map. It had not been built as a separate line, but was merged from different sections of the Metropolitan Line and the District Line. Only two short sections of this line are solely used by the Circle line. These sections are the connecting curves between the stations of High Street Kensington and Gloucester Road and between Aldgate and Tower Hill.","popularity":1.0,"category":0,"screenshots":[{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/frpzyoep0lcqhxezoymx.jpg","cloudinary_id":"frpzyoep0lcqhxezoymx","width":833,"height":533},{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/tubo3hsysnzoplsvccnb.jpg","cloudinary_id":"tubo3hsysnzoplsvccnb","width":1000,"height":560},{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/c1qwqnupkar1nuuuhgud.jpg","cloudinary_id":"c1qwqnupkar1nuuuhgud","width":1018,"height":572}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/guha9akgcdfsd17at5ku.jpg","cloudinary_id":"guha9akgcdfsd17at5ku","width":828,"height":1200}},{"id":50411,"name":"Val and Rick","slug":"val-and-rick","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/val-and-rick","created_at":1500041381426,"updated_at":1500462468561,"popularity":1.333333333333333,"category":0,"genres":[5],"first_release_date":1113350400000,"platforms":[6],"release_dates":[{"ca