cks in that same level. Losing consecutive duels results in decreased difficulty for the first time in Power of Chaos games. Other options include allowing the opponent to use cards from the previous two games, increasing the difficulty. Also, the option to make many Limited cards Forbidden is given, making the game more balanced. One other new addition to the game is that when you win cards that you already have, you may have a choice of getting different cards, or keep the ones you've earned. This can only be done when every card you win in a match or one card in a single duel is a common card, not new. Last, you can also duel a friend via LAN or via Gameranger.","collection":5167,"franchise":57,"franchises":[57],"rating":78.2131987231831,"popularity":2.0,"total_rating":78.2131987231831,"total_rating_count":6,"rating_count":6,"games":[23467,50834,26893,31559,932,15707,4108,27209,6699,26841],"tags":[268435465,268435471,268435472,536870990,536871208,536871213,536871327,536874083,536874694,536875054,536875126,536875467,536875525,536875586,536876232,536877755],"developers":[129],"publishers":[129],"category":0,"keywords":[78,296,301,415,3171,3782,4142,4214,4555,4613,4674,5320,6843],"genres":[9,15,16],"first_release_date":1088726400000,"platforms":[6],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":6,"date":1088726400000,"region":8,"human":"2004-Jul-02","y":2004,"m":7}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/glirhoakc994bw42bieo.jpg","cloudinary_id":"glirhoakc994bw42bieo","width":640,"height":909},"esrb":{"rating":3},"pegi":{"rating":1}},{"id":50834,"name":"Yu-Gi-Oh! Power of Chaos: Yugi the Destiny","slug":"yu-gi-oh-power-of-chaos-yugi-the-destiny","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/yu-gi-oh-power-of-chaos-yugi-the-destiny","created_at":1500054518860,"updated_at":1527707953962,"summary":"The first Yu-Gi-Oh! game for PC and the first of the three Power of Chaos games. The game includes 155 cards which most of them are from Legend of Blue Eyes White Dragon