d movie \"The Many Adventures of Winnie the Pooh\"and Chapter 9 of A.A. Milne's book Winnie-the-Pooh.). The game has no animation in the mode of a traditional Quest game such as King's Quest. Rather, the Hundred Acre Wood existed as a grid of connected static screens. Players move between the screen using the arrow keys and can only move North, South, East or West. The missing items are randomly assigned at the start of each new game to screens within this grid, although the various characters can always be found on the same screens. When an item is \"dropped\" on a screen in order to \"pick up\" another item, the dropped item stays on that screen until the user returns to retrieve it later. \nReuniting a character with their item results in a celebration screen.","collection":2986,"popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[13189,22425,25222,41895,55803,26766,47823,36926,11296,19289],"tags":[268435487,536871208,536871939,536872475,536875054,536875078,536875243,536875291,536875292,536877280,536881400],"category":0,"keywords":[296,1027,1563,4142,4166,4331,4379,4380,6368,10488],"genres":[31],"first_release_date":507600000000,"platforms":[6],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":6,"date":507600000000,"region":8,"human":"1986-Feb-01","y":1986,"m":2}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/onp0xarhxnzjafbpabf1.jpg","cloudinary_id":"onp0xarhxnzjafbpabf1","width":350,"height":418}},{"id":51371,"name":"Space Bunnies Must Die!","slug":"space-bunnies-must-die","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/space-bunnies-must-die","created_at":1500065349553,"updated_at":1515663224158,"summary":"Space Bunnies Must Die! is a third-person action-adventure game developed by Ripcord Games and released on October 31, 1998 by Jinx for Microsoft Windows 98. The game was going to be released on the Nintendo 64 in 1999, but it got cancelled. Player character is truck stop waitress and rodeo performer Allison Huxley, who must save the world and her abducted sister from an invadin